Low density of historic materials, minor Orange, moderate St. Johns, aceramic below aprox. 1 foot according to Moore's field notes.
Orange through St. Johns limited to upper 50 cm of deposits across site, deposits below 50 cm are Mount Taylor period in age and lack pottery.
Orange and St. Johns primarily in shell-free deposits across site but also in shell-bearing deposits on western edge of site. Eastern edge of site has shell free Mt. Taylor deposits.
